    "may cause the gradient disappearance, which means that smoothing occurs during backpropagation, i.e., the features of all nodes in the graph converge to the same value.",
    "Thus, GCNs are generally shallow structures that contain 2-3 graph convolutional layers.",
    "Shallow structures limit the performance of the model, because they cannot mine higher-order node information.",
    "Gradient disappearance poses a challenge for the deep GCNs designing.",
    "Gradient disappearance is also a significant factor limiting the training of deep CNNs models."
